# April (Fallen Survival / Project Vector)

Before implementing or fixing anything in this repo, read **`April/AGENTS.md`**.

## Required reading every session

1. **`April/AGENTS.md`** — project architecture, build flow, rules
2. **`April/docs/API.md`** — Vector Lua API (draw, menu, entity, images). **Read the Images section before any image work. Do not guess API signatures.**
3. **`April/references/dump/GAME_REFERENCE.txt`** — workspace folders, modules, remotes
4. **`April/references/dump/`** — verify instance names, paths, scripts when adding ESP/scans/hooks
5. **`fallen_legacy.lua`** + **`April/docs/LEGACY_FEATURES.md`** — when porting or matching old behavior

## Quick constraints

- Edit `April/src/`, run `node April/scripts/bundle.mjs`, sync to `April/Script 1.lua`
- Draw/menu reads happen per-frame; use `settings.enabled()` for checkboxes
- `draw.load_image` is async — check `draw.image_loaded` before `draw.image`; lazy-load in `on_frame` via `image_cache.tick_all`
- Item/Tung icons use **GitHub HTTPS CDN** (`assets/` → raw.githubusercontent.com) — run `npm run assets` after dump changes
- Fallen anti-cheat: **no WalkSpeed writes** — use legacy velocity omnisprint pattern
- ESP folder paths must match dump (`Nodes`, `Drops`, `Military`, etc.)

When unsure about game structure, **grep the dump** (`instances.jsonl`, `GAME_REFERENCE.txt`) before coding.
